*"For everything there is a season, and a time for 
every matter under heaven."*{Ecclesiastes 3:1}{The book of nature is written 
in the language of mathematics.}{Galileo Galilei}

**The Six Functions.** Sine and cosine are defined by the unit circle; 
the other four are derived from them:
\[
 \tan\theta = \frac{\sin\theta}{\cos\theta} \qquad \cot\theta = \frac{\cos\theta}{\sin\theta} \qquad \sec\theta = \frac{1}{\cos\theta} \qquad \csc\theta = \frac{1}{\sin\theta}
\]
